  "text": "Django URL routing in this version (6.1 alpha) uses a modern pattern-based system rather than the deprecated patterns() function from pre-1.10 Django. The main URL routing components are:\n\n## Core URL Routing Files:\n\n1. **django/urls/conf.py**: Contains the main URL definition functions:\n   - `include(arg, namespace=None)`: Function to include URL patterns from another module, supporting both module strings and list/tuple objects for namespace configuration\n   - `_path(route, view, kwargs, name, Pattern)`: Internal base function for URL pattern creation\n   - `path()` and `re_path()`: Partial functions that create RoutePattern and RegexPattern respectively\n\n2. **django/urls/resolvers.py**: The URL dispatcher engine containing:\n   - `URLResolver`: The main class that resolves URLs to views by recursively matching against url_patterns\n   - `URLPattern`: Represents a single URL pattern with callback view\n   - `ResolverMatch`: Result object returned when a URL successfully resolves\n   - `RoutePattern`: Pattern class for path()-style routes with converters (simple, readable syntax)\n   - `RegexPattern`: Pattern class for re_path()-style routes with regular expressions\n   - `LocalePrefixPattern`: Special pattern for i18n URL prefixing\n   - `_route_to_regex()`: Converts simple path routes to regex for matching\n   - `get_resolver()`: Caches and returns the root URLResolver for a given urlconf\n\n3. **django/urls/base.py**: Core URL utility functions:\n   - `resolve(path, urlconf)`: Matches a URL path and returns a ResolverMatch\n   - `reverse(viewname, urlconf, args, kwargs)`: Generates URLs from view names\n   - `set_urlconf()/get_urlconf()`: Thread-local URL configuration management\n\n4. **django/urls/converters.py**: Path parameter type converters:\n   - `IntConverter`, `StringConverter`, `UUIDConverter`, `SlugConverter`, `PathConverter`\n   - `register_converter()`: Allows custom converter registration\n\n5. **django/conf/urls/i18n.py**: Internationalization support:\n   - `i18n_patterns(*urls, prefix_default_language)`: Wraps URL patterns with language prefix\n   - Uses `LocalePrefixPattern` to handle language code prefixing\n\n6. **django/conf/urls/static.py**: Static file serving:\n   - `static(prefix, view)`: Convenience function to serve static files during development\n\n## URL Pattern Flow:\n\nThe URL routing system works as follows:\n\n1. User defines `urlpatterns = [path(...), include(...), re_path(...), ...]` in a URL configuration module\n2. The root `URLResolver` loads these patterns via `get_resolver()`\n3. When a request comes in, `resolve(path)` is called which:\n   - Recursively calls `URLResolver.resolve()` to match against patterns\n   - Each pattern's `match()` method checks if the path matches\n   - For URLResolvers (include()), recursively resolves the remaining path\n4. Returns a `ResolverMatch` with the view, args, kwargs, and metadata\n\n## Key Differences from patterns():\n\nThe deprecated `patterns()` function from pre-1.10 Django is not present. Instead:\n- Modern Django uses direct list assignment: `urlpatterns = [...]`\n- The `include()` function now accepts module paths and tuple notation for namespacing\n- Path converters in `path()` provide type conversion and validation\n- The URL dispatcher (URLResolver) handles both legacy regex patterns and modern simplified paths\n\nAll URL configuration files can coexist with urlpatterns defined as simple Python lists, and the URLResolver intelligently processes both RoutePattern (path-style) and RegexPattern (re_path-style) URLs."
}

